# Cortex umbrella — transient tool state, not project history.
#
# This file ships with the cortex/ umbrella so these ignore rules travel to
# every repo the agentic layer runs in, independent of the host repo's root
# .gitignore (which carries the `.cortex-init` / `.cortex-init-backup/` markers
# and `.claude/worktrees/`, plus the all-or-nothing `# cortex/` toggle). Paths
# below are relative to this cortex/ directory.
#
# Already-committed copies of these artifacts in existing repos are not
# untracked by this file — git only applies ignore rules to untracked paths.
#
# A `**` prefix matches at active-feature AND archive depth
# (`lifecycle/<slug>/...` and `lifecycle/archive/<slug>/...`). Rules stay
# basename-scoped to transient artifacts so sibling work-products (e.g.
# `learnings/outline.md`) are never swept. Negation (`!path`) rules would be
# inert once the root `# cortex/` toggle is uncommented (git can't re-include
# under an ignored parent), so this file uses none.

# Lifecycle ephemeral session / lock files
lifecycle/**/.session
lifecycle/**/.session-owner
lifecycle/**/.dispatching
lifecycle/**/.lock

# Lifecycle runtime artifacts
lifecycle/**/agent-activity.jsonl
lifecycle/**/learnings/recovery-log.md
lifecycle/overnight-events*.log
lifecycle/metrics.json
lifecycle/sessions/

# Critical-review residue — written for the morning report, read off-disk by
# overnight/report.py (never via git), so it is transient working-tree scratch.
lifecycle/**/critical-review-residue.json

# Backlog audit log + regenerated index cache
backlog/*.events.jsonl
backlog/index.json
backlog/index.md

# Ad-hoc critical-review snapshots (pruned by cortex-clean --adhoc)
_adhoc/
